  "source": "{title: Top Of The World}\n{artist: Carpenters}\n{key: F}\n{reviewed: true}\n\n{section: Verse 1}\nS[F]uch a feelings comin[C]g over [Bb]me  [F]  \nThere is won[Am]der in most ever[Gm]ythi[C7]ng I s[F]ee  [F7] \nNot a cl[Bb]oud in the sk[C]y\nGot the sun[Am] in my ey[D]es\nAnd I wo[Gm7]n't be surp[Bbm7]rised if it's a dre[C]am  [C7]\n[F]Everything I wa[C]nt the wo[Bb]rld to [F]be\n            \nIs now com[Am]ing true espe[Gm]ciall[C7]y for m[F]e  [F7]\nAnd the re[Bb]ason is cl[C]ear, it's beca[Am]use you are her[D]e\nYou're the nea[Gm7]rest thing to heav[Bbm7]en that I've seen[C7]\n\n{section: Chorus}\nI'm on the to[F]p of the world looking d[Bb]own on creation\nAnd the o[F]nly explanat[Bb]ion I c[C7]an fi[F]nd [F7]\nIs the lov[Bb]e that I've foun[C7]d ever since [F]you've been a[Bb]round\nYour love's p[F]ut me at the top [Gm7]of the[C7] world[F]\n\n{section: Verse 2}\nSomething in the wind has learned my name\nAnd it's telling me that things are not the same\nIn the leaves on the trees\nAnd the touch of the breeze\nThere's a pleasing sense of happiness for me\nThere is only one wish on my mind\nWhen this day is through I hope that I will find\nThat tomorrow will be just the same for you and me\nAll I need will be mine if you are here\n"
